text: The University of Wisconsin–Green Bay is a public university in Green Bay, Wisconsin, and a part of the University of Wisconsin System. The university has about 6,549 students. It was founded in 1965. The current chancellor of the university is Michael Alexander. ==Sports== The university calls itself "Green Bay" for sports purposes, and its teams use the nickname of Phoenix. The school has 16 varsity teams that compete in the Horizon League. ==Other websites== *University of Wisconsin–Green Bay's Official website *Green Bay Phoenix official athletics website Green Bay Green Bay Category:Green Bay, Wisconsin Category:1965 establishments in the United States Category:1960s establishments in Wisconsin
